==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[uzdaz]]'', from Indo-European ''ŭes-'' ‘[[stab]]’. Germanic cognates include Middle Dutch ''ort'' (Dutch ''[[oord]]''), Old High German ''[[ort]]'' (German ''[[Ort]]''), Old Norse ''[[oddr]]'' (Icelandic ''[[oddur]]'', Old Swedish ''odder'', Swedish ''[[udd]]'', Danish ''[[od]]'').
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ord/
===Noun===
'''ord''' {{m}} ({{p}} [[ordas]])
# a [[point]], especially of a weapon
# a point of origin, a [[beginning]]

